    <node id="Los Angeles">
      <data key="d0">Los Angeles</data>
      <data key="d1">location</data>
      <data key="d2">Los Angeles is a major city located in the state of California, United States. It is notable for being the residence of Gigi Causey and the headquarters of Korn Ferry, a prominent global organizational consulting firm. The city has also been the deathplace of several notable individuals, including Lee Mantle, who moved to Los Angeles in 1921 and passed away there in 1934. Other individuals who died in Los Angeles include Roy Mack, Reginald Le Borg, John Francis Dillon, Scott R. Dunlap in 1970, and William C. McGann. These connections highlight Los Angeles's significance as both a cultural hub and a place of historical importance for various prominent figures.&lt;SEP&gt;Los Angeles is the place where Robert Thornby died.&lt;SEP&gt;Los Angeles is where Jerzy Skolimowski lived for over 20 years.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1bfb07eaab27897458cab13d267cc8d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a4c2c97ee31ddb939c8237c792d072f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1c964718d02482f357275fdf774f6b32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5bec0e24884c0a0461e84d64ffcd5daf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-111baa2ee096c8d9e17d6d344931bb5e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9253bb30965391f200c7ac54d0182647&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7209ac7a04cb03c6f62da54fda33a7e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-afca04bc65f35690d7be4303cbb67e22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-859b67c318a0eb94d1cc6fdecd189e28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b1f0748daa6aa0f14a8e76004cdb149</data>
