    <node id="Prince Napoléon Bonaparte">
      <data key="d0">Prince Napoléon Bonaparte</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Prince Napoléon Bonaparte, also known as Napoléon-Jérôme Bonaparte or Jérôme Bonaparte, was the second son of Jerome, King of Westphalia, and Catharina of Württemberg. He was an outspoken liberal and became the de facto head of the House of Bonaparte from 1879 until his death.</data>
