    <node id="Tivala">
      <data key="d0">Tivala</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Tivala, also known as Tivara, was a son of Maurya Emperor Ashoka from his second queen, Karuvaki. He is the only son of Ashoka mentioned by name in his inscriptions and was the favorite child and probable crown prince.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c441fc08420b5ae39ad39901be0e214c</data>
