      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Tsandzile Ndwandwe, also known as LaZidze, was the "Ndlovukati" or senior queen of Swaziland from July 1868 until June 1875. She was the daughter of Zwide kaLanga, the senior wife of Sobhuza I, and the mother of Mswati II.</data>
