      <data key="d2">Louis, Dauphin of France was the son of Queen Marie Leszczyńska.&lt;SEP&gt;Marie Leszczyńska, also known as Maria Karolina Zofia Felicja Leszczyńska, was a Polish princess and French queen consort. She was the daughter of King Stanisław Leszczyński and Catherine Opalińska, and she married King Louis XV of France. She served as queen consort of France for 42 years from 1725 until her death in 1768.</data>
