    </node>
    <node id="Henry Beauchamp Oliver St John">
      <data key="d0">Henry Beauchamp Oliver St John</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Henry Beauchamp Oliver St John, 18th Baron St John of Bletso, was an English peer, eldest son of Beauchamp St John, 17th Baron St John of Bletso, and Helen Thornton. He was educated at Wellington College and Magdalene College, Cambridge. He became the 18th Baron St John in 1912, inherited Melchbourne Park, and served as a JP for Bedfordshire. He died unmarried at the age of 44 and was succeeded by his younger brother, Moubray.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed0f367903882fbe399a1ac038eea2bd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1782061246</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Beauchamp St John">
      <data key="d0">Beauchamp St John</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Beauchamp Moubray St John, 17th Baron St John of Bletso, was an English peer. He was born at Melchbourne, the second son of St Andrew St John, 15th Baron St John of Bletso, and Eleanor Hussey. He served in the Highland Light Infantry until 1867. He inherited the title Baron St John of Bletso in 1887 and moved to Melchbourne Park, Bedfordshire. He served as Lord Lieutenant of Bedfordshire from 1905 to 1912. He married Helen Charlotte Thornton in 1869 and had a large family. His eldest son Henry succeeded to the title, followed by his second son Mowbray. He married secondly to Ethel Susan Lutley in 1911.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed0f367903882fbe399a1ac038eea2bd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1782061246</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Beauchamp St John, 17th Baron St John of Bletso">
      <data key="d0">Beauchamp St John, 17th Baron St John of Bletso</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Beauchamp St John, 17th Baron St John of Bletso, was the father of Henry Beauchamp Oliver St John, 18th Baron St John of Bletso. He died in 1912, and his son Henry succeeded him as the 18th Baron St John.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed0f367903882fbe399a1ac038eea2bd</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1782061246</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Helen Thornton">
      <data key="d0">Helen Thornton</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Helen Thornton was the wife of Beauchamp St John, 17th Baron St John of Bletso, and the mother of Henry Beauchamp Oliver St John, 18th Baron St John of Bletso. She died in 1909.</data>
