    <edge source="World Athletics Federation" target="Noah Carter">
      <data key="d7">253.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The relationship between Noah Carter and the World Athletics Federation centers on the validation of Carter's athletic record by the governing body. The World Athletics Federation, formerly known as the International Association of Athletics Federations (IAAF), is responsible for overseeing and sanctioning athletic records globally. The validation of Noah Carter's record signifies that his achievement meets the standards and criteria set by the federation. This process ensures the authenticity and legitimacy of Carter's performance, confirming its compliance with established regulations and protocols. The recognition by the World Athletics Federation underscores the significance of Carter's achievement within the realm of competitive athletics, highlighting its importance and credibility in the sport. Multiple sources consistently affirm that Noah Carter's record has been validated by the World Athletics Federation, reinforcing the legitimacy and recognition of his athletic accomplishment.&lt;SEP&gt;Noah Carter's record is validated by the World Athletics Federation.&lt;SEP&gt;Noah Carter's record is validated by the World Athletics Federation.&lt;SEP&gt;Noah Carter's record is validated by the World Athletics Federation.&lt;SEP&gt;Noah Carter's record is validated by the World Athletics Federation.&lt;SEP&gt;Noah Carter's record is validated by the World Athletics Federation.</data>
